main event: On November 12, 1966, a civilian reported observing a dome-like object traveling at a constant speed in the northeastern sky.
interesting points: The object was described as the size of small stars in the sky, It appeared to have a consistent light source that was neither pulsating nor flashing, The object was observed for 90 seconds before vanishing, A lady reported seeing 3 or 4 bright lights moving in a diamond pattern, Another sighting involved a very bright light changing colors that hovered and moved erratically for 30 minutes.
witness description: A civilian who reported the sighting.
